   &UR; NATIONAL _ GENERAL (Moved in ``a'' category) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   NYMAYOR-FUNDRAISING _ Mayor Rudolph Giuliani is raising money
for other Republicans in Wisconsin and Iowa, where the question
centers on his political plans. Many Iowans seem impressed when he
notes that the number of murders in New York City has declined
during his tenure to 800 a year from 2,000. Many also say they are
familiar with the mayor through his appearances on David Letterman
and the Tonight Show. By Dan Barry.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WASHINGTON _ (Moved in ``w'' category)  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   FUNDRAISING-GORE _ Attorney General Janet Reno advances a step
closer to asking for an independent prosecutor to investigate Vice
President Al Gore's role in fund raising for the 1996 campaign by
ordering a 90-day preliminary inquiry into whether Gore lied to
investigators last year when he was initially interviewed about his
telephone solicitations from the White House. By David Johnston.
</P>
