<P>
   PALSY-COMPUTER _ For maybe 20 years, Scott Meece imagined a
wondrous day when he could write by talking to a computer and read
by listening to it speak. Now Meece has a computer setup that talks
and listens. (Lamb, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   HOMEWORK-SPACE _ A structured study area can turn homework woes
into successes, experts say. One of the key areas parents may
consider changing is the time, place and space their children do
their homework. Experts agree it's a good idea to set up consistent
study areas in a quiet and visible place in the house. (Mays, Waco
Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   PSYCHOLOGY-COLUMN _ Psychotherapy is generally thought of as a
verbal rather than medicinal approach to helping individuals with
psychological difficulties. In clinical practice, psychotherapy and
medication are often used together to help treat individuals with
emotional difficulties, such as depression and anxiety. (LeCrone,
Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   WARNER-ON-WOOD _ For those of you not up to your hips in the
Internet, FAQ means a list of answers to Frequently Asked
Questions. It's little wonder that the following gentlemen didn't
get any satisfaction there; his is scarcely a frequently asked
question. And for those of you who, like this inquirer, aren't
woodworkers, ``forms and jigs'' are shopmade devices used to speed
or otherwise aid in construction. (Warner, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   DENTIST-RC _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ When Dr. Steven Harris'
hands aren't earning him a living in his West Palm Beach dentistry
practice, they're usually involved with his hobby du jour. But
these amusements, the family agrees, are mere dalliances beside the
sustaining passions of his life. ``I'm an RC modeler,'' Harris, 52,
declares without remorse. ``I build and fly radio-control aircraft.
I'm a member of the Palm Beach Aero Club. We fly them at the
fairgrounds and at a field in Stuart.'' (Wiggins, Palm Beach Post)
MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   VANITY-PLATE _ When Mary Lou Janke's first grandchild, Brent
Sykora, was learning to talk, he just couldn't pronounce Granny,
which is what Janke wanted him to call her. He could say Grammy,
and that evolved into Gween. When Sykora was about 4, he started
calling his grandmother Dween. That name stuck, and Janke applied
for a personalized, or vanity, license plate that read DWEEN. That
was about 20 years ago. Sykora is now 23 and has two siblings:
Blake, 19; and Shelley, 14. Today, in honor of the three
grandchildren, Janke's plate says DWEEN 3. (Tankersley, Waco
Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SCIENCE/MEDICINE/ENVIRONMENT (a and/or l category)
</P>
<P>
   WHALE _ SEWALL'S POINT, Fla. _ An off-duty Martin County
sheriff's deputy, boaters and teenagers came to the aid of a sick
pygmy sperm whale that beached itself on the south side of the
Stuart Causeway on a recent afternoon. ``I've never seen a whale
strand in the Indian River before,'' said Erik Martin of Ecological
Associates, head of the local marine mammal stranding network.
``It's a freak thing. The whale must have come in the (Stuart)
inlet.'' (Swartz, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
