 ART ADV.: Photos with HAITIAN-SCHOLAR, QUEBECOIS-BEACH, and
GARDEN-COLUMN are being transmitted to NYT Photo Service
subscribers.  
 For Immediate Release  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move the following FEATURE stories for
use by NYTimes News Service clients.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, contact  &UR; Frank Perrotta  &LR; at the
Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of graphics
or photos please call 212 556-4204 or -1927.
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   PAKISTAN-US (Hong Kong) -- The last three decades have been
punctuated by conflict between the United States and Pakistan,
which has felt abandoned by Washington during two wars with India.
Then the Clinton administration imposed economic sanctions on
Islamabad for testing nuclear weapons. By Indira A.R. Lakshmanan.
1450 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
