<HEADLINE>
AWASH IN PHILOSOPHY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: Why does Dr. Bronner's Pure-Castile Soap have strange sayings
and political statements all over its packaging?
</P>
<P>
   _ L.S., Haltom City, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: According to interviews, the labels are used to present Dr.
Emanuel H. Bronner's philosophical and spiritual beliefs because no
one else would publish them.
</P>
<P>
   A sample: ``Absolute cleanliness is Godliness, teach the Moral
ABC that unites all mankind free, lightning like, 5 billion strong
and we're One.''
</P>
<P>
   ``The amount of philosophy you get is proportional to the size
of the container,'' William Poundstone writes in ``Bigger
Secrets.''
</P>
<P>
   Bronner, who began selling Dr. Bronner's Peppermint Soap in
1949, died in March 1997 at age 89. His soaps and other products
can be found in many health food stores.
</P>
<P>
   Q: How can I get my name off of mail and telephone marketing
lists?
</P>
<P>
   _ M.L., Fort Myers, Fla.
</P>
<P>
   A: To reduce the amount of nonprofit and commercial mail you
receive, send your name and address to: Mail Preference Service,
Direct Marketing Association, Box 9008, Farmingdale, NY 11735-9008.
</P>
<P>
   The DMA offers a similar do-not-call phone service. Send your
name, address and telephone number to: Telephone Preference
Service, Direct Marketing Association, Box 9014, Farmingdale, NY
11735-9014.
</P>
<P>
   These services reduce the amount of mail and phone calls but
don't eliminate them completely. Numerous national direct-marketing
companies participate in the programs, but their use is voluntary.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Help settle a disagreement: How long has the comic strip
``Tank McNamara'' been published?
</P>
<P>
   _ S.O., River Vale, N.J.
</P>
<P>
   A: The sports strip was launched in 1974 by two contributors to
the Houston Chronicle, writer Jeff Millar and artist Bill Hinds.
</P>
<P>
   Write to Millar and Hinds in care of Andrews McMeel Universal,
4520 Main St., Kansas City, MO 64111-7701, or send e-mail to
millar-hinds(at)worldnet.att.net.
</P>
<P>
   Universal maintains an official Tank Web site at
www.uexpress.com.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
