   BE-BOP (New York _ Change often registers as sound before it is
fully assimilated as culture. Be-bop was the electrifying
first-time translation of post-Depression America into musical
language, and its creators found in New York their capital. The
only place he would be willing to live if he couldn't live in New
York, Thelonious Monk said, was the moon. By Ann Douglas.
</P>
<P>
   QUINN-THEATER-REVIEW (New York) _ Given his prominent television
comedy job, as the new anchor of ``Weekend Update'' on ``Saturday
Night Live,'' you might have assumed that ``Colin Quinn: An Irish
Wake,'' which opened last night, would be a satirical spinoff of
his late-night showcase. But if you were expecting a standup comic,
a Seinfeldesque brush with Broadway, fuhgeddaboutit. What you get
in Quinn instead is an honest-to-goodness seanachai, an Irish
storyteller, a weaver of legends. By Peter Marks.
