<P>
   ATTN SPORTS EDITORS: The Little League team from Greenville,
N.C., plays in the U.S. finals of the Little League World Series
tonight at 8 p.m., after a come-from-behind victory over Cypress,
Calif., Wednesday in Willampsort, Pa. If the Greenville team wins,
it will go to the final game against the international winner
Saturday at 3:30 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   The Daily Reflector in Greenville, a Cox newspaper, is covering
with two writers and a photographer and will move stories and post
photos. Stories and photos will move late tonight, and if they win,
late Saturday afternoon. For more information, please call CoxNet
at 404-526-5456.
</P>
