<P>
   &UR; COMPUTERS (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   COMPUTERS-COLUMN (Undated) _ The new iMac computer from Apple is
selling faster than Powerball tickets, sales that have given Apple
a big boost, at least among the Mac faithful. By Hiawatha Bray.
</P>
<P>
   COMPUTERS-IBM (Undated) -- Now that we're all comfortable with
the idea of buying really cheap home computers, IBM is stepping out
with a bold new strategy -- selling really expensive home
computers. By Hiawatha Bray. 400 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   TIMBERLAND-HYBRID (Undated) -- Timberland calls them ``beige
shoes,'' a hybrid between sneakers and hiking boots. Whatever the
type, they're a key component in Timberland's effort to get back on
track. By Chris Reidy. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   ONBUSINESS-COLUMN (Undated) _ Former Massacahusetts treasurer
Bob Crane invested $5 million in pension funds in a losing
Hollywood deal. Now the state has recovered the money, plus
interest. By Steven Syre and Steve Bailey.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS &LR;   &UR; (s) &LR;
