get impatient in the express checkout line at my favorite
Albertsons and count the items in the cart of the customer ahead of
me _ especially if there are two or three more customers in front
of him. And, I may get annoyed and huff and puff a little when I
get stuck in traffic _ but I'm not cynical, much less hostile.
Maybe, maybe not, says a researcher affiliated with Duke
University's Behavioral Medicine Research Center. By CAROLYN
