   BIZ-BOOKS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Microsoft Corp. may face its biggest challenge ever
when it squares off in court next month against Justice Department
attorneys who charge that the software giant illegally leveraged
its monopoly position to extend its dominance. But the seeds for
the government's antitrust case against the maker of the Windows
computer operating system were planted more than four years ago
when Silicon Valley start-up Netscape Communications Corp. launched
its efforts to make the Internet appealing to mainstream computer
users. By TERESA McUSIC. Story has moved in ``f'' financial
category &QL;
