<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    `Unmarried ... With Child' but no bimbo
 &HT;    By Phil Kloer
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   This week we've been profiling TV stars who became famous in one
series, and will be coming back this fall in a new series with a
new character. This is our final profile.
</P>
<P>
   -- Who: Christina Applegate
</P>
<P>
   -- Best known as: Kelly Bundy, one of the most memorably dim
blond bimbos in TV history on ``Married ... With Children.'' Tight
of dress, vacant of stare and beloved of adolescent boys (of all
ages) for the show's 11-year run.
</P>
<P>
   -- Next known as: Jesse Warner, a decent, hard-working single
mother on NBC's new sitcom ``Jesse.'' It's from the creators of
``Friends'' and airs between ``Friends'' and ``Frasier'' at 8:30
p.m. ET, Thursdays starting Sept. 24. Can you say ``guaranteed
hit''?
</P>
<P>
   -- Dramatic stretch: Enormous. There isn't the slightest trace
of Kelly Bundy in Jesse _ or in Applegate either, who's serious and
down to earth.
</P>
<P>
   -- Between shows: Played the Diane Keaton role in ``Mafia!,''
this summer's ``Godfather'' spoof. Also had a small role in ``Mars
Attacks!'' Stars in independent film ``Claudine's Return,'' not yet
released.
</P>
<P>
   -- Looking back: ```Married ... With Children' was closer to a
cartoon than anything else,'' she says. ``A lot of the jokes were
done for shock value. I don't have any resentments toward it
whatsoever. It was a wonderful 11 years of my life.''
</P>
<P>
   -- Her image as Kelly Bundy: ``It's never really hit me that the
show is out there, as massive as it is. I've kept very grounded and
very private.''
</P>
<P>
   -- Incidentally: ``I was also raised by a single mother, so I
had firsthand training as far as that's concerned.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
