<P>
   BOEING-EXPLOSION (Seattle) The aftermath of Boeing Delta III
explosion. Experts say Boeing has a lost a golden opportunity to
take the early lead in the lucrative launch business over European
and Chinese competitors with last night's dramatic failure of its
new heavy lift rocket that cost more than $1.5 billion to develop.
What happens now depends on the investigation. If it's a simple
fix, Delta III could be ready again within 4-6 months. If a design
flaw, the program could be facing a long and potentially
devastating setback. Boeing said data shows rocket began to go out
of control 55 seconds into flight and was then blown up. Boeing's
stock down slightly today, and analysts say it will loose less than
a half cent per share of revenue after taxes as a result of the
Delta 3 setback. But the stock of PanAmSat, the satellite's owner,
is down more than 17 percent after the company said it would cost
the firm about $200 million in revenues this year. Satellite was
insured, this is just revenue loss.
</P>
