   FAA-AIR-SAFETY (Washington) _ The manufacturer of a commuter
plane that crashed near Detroit in January 1997 had written a new
procedure that probably would have prevented the accident, which
was caused by ice, but the information got lost between two
branches of the FAA, and no one instructed the pilots, the NTSB
says. By Matthew L. Wald.
</P>
<P>
   Reefers: HURRICANE-BONNIE (Wilmington, N.C.) _ Bonnie is
downgraded to a tropical storm as it drags itself slowly across
eastern North Carolina, pouring up to 10 inches of rain on parts of
the coastal plain. By Kevin Sack.
</P>
