   GRAPEFRUIT _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ While the value of land
used to grow citrus continues to fall statewide, grapefruit growers
have been hardest hit, according to a survey by the University of
Florida. The value of grapefruit groves in the southern part of the
state fell 25 percent to $3,035 an acre this year, while the value
for orange groves fell less than 6 percent to $6,882 an acre.
(Waresh, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
