<P>
   NCR-HISTORY _ MONTGOMERY COUNTY, Ohio _ Industrialist John H.
Patterson liked to boast that wherever men traded, a National cash
register was tracking the transaction. A photographer on the NCR
payroll often was not far behind, making images of the famous,
Dayton-made machinery in remote places worldwide. Those images _
400,000 photographic negatives on glass from 1895 forward _ are
among the treasures NCR announced that it will lend to the
Montgomery County, Ohio, Historical Society. (Kline, Dayton Daily
News) MOVED.
