<P>
   &QL; 
BABBITT (Washington) - Grand jury subpeonas have begun to fly in
the indepdendent counsel investigation of Interior Secretary Bruce
Babbitt. The requests for documents have Interior employees
scouring four years worth of e-mail and pulling records on nearly
every instance of taking land in trust for Indian tribes. The
Burton Committee has turned over reams of paper it collected in its
investigation, and its staff has met with some of the nine
principle investigating attorneys hired by Carol Elder Bruce. One
attorney's hiring in particular has been questioned by
conservatives concerned about his ties to Democrats, but that
hasn't slowed the probe, which is on the fast-track, sources say,
to a determination by the end of the year. By ADRIANNE FLYNN. Story
will move in the ``A`` category. &QL; 
