<P>
   TEXAS-SCANDAL (Austin, Texas) _ A state housing official
appointed by Gov. George W. Bush is under investigation by the FBI
for accepting a bribe for her vote in favor of a questionable
low-income housing deal. The official, Florita Bell Griffin of
Bryan, was appointed by Bush in 1995 and continues to serve on the
nine-member board of the Texas Department of Housing and Community
Affairs. Griffin says she is innocent and wrongly accused. By POLLY
ROSS HUGHES.
