<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR FRIDAY, AUGUST 28
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Friday. Days and dates refer to the original article's transmission
by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be adjusted by
NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-LIBYA-LOCKERBIE-NYT (moved on Wednesday, August 26)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, August
26, about Libya's response to a proposal to bring two suspects to
trial in the 1988 bombing of a Pan Am jet over Lockerbie, Scotland,
misstated the nature of economic sanctions against Libya. The
country is prohibited from importing certain items, not from
exporting them.
</P>
<P>
   BC-AFRICA-SECURITY-NYT (moved on Friday, August 7)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Friday, August 7,
about security standards at American embassies and a chart that day
showing the time line of attacks on American targets abroad
misstated the number of deaths in a bombing in Lebanon in September
1984. Similar errors appeared in a chart on Aug. 9 and an article
on Aug. 10 about the Administration's urging increased spending for
embassy security.
</P>
<P>
   The number of deaths has never been precisely determined, but it
is 14 to 24.
</P>
<P>
   BC-MEDIA-TALK-NYT (moved on Sunday, August 16)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, August 16,
about a change in the international edition of The Miami Herald
described the plan incorrectly. The existing version will be
replaced by a shortened version of the Miami edition; the
international edition is not ending.
</P>
</TEXT>
