</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    On Deck: St. Louis Cardinals
 &HT;    By Thomas Stinson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   When: 8:05 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Where: Busch Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   TV/radio: TBS, 750-AM.
</P>
<P>
   Probable starting pitchers: RHP Greg Maddux (17-6, 1.91; 17-14,
2.39 lifetime vs. Cardinals) vs. LHP Kent Mercker (8-11, 5.57; 1-2,
5.04 lifetime vs. Braves).
</P>
<P>
   Notes: When the Braves traded Mercker on Dec. 17, 1995, for the
since departed Joe Borowski and Rachaad Stewart, he was coming off
a 7-8 season, his worst as a Brave. In more than five years of
service with the Braves, Mercker had gone 31-25 with a 3.49 ERA.
Now with his fourth club in three years, Mercker has gone 20-28
since, with a 5.17 ERA. Even so, he faces the Braves as the
winningest pitcher of the depleted Cardinals' staff with just eight
victories. He defeated the Braves for the first time in four tries
when he last faced them July 31, beating Greg Maddux 3-2. Maddux is
coming off one of the worst starts in his career: three homers and
seven earned runs allowed in five innings to Los Angeles on
Sunday). He is 5-4 in the second half and hasn't won consecutive
games since beating Toronto and Tampa Bay on June 27 and July 2.
For all that, he still can become the National League's first
18-game winner tonight. He is 10-6 lifetime at Busch Stadium.
</P>
